commentary: Imad Wasim to de Villiers, OUT AB's gone first ball. What? Wow. South Africa in tatters. Flat and wide from Imad. It does nothing but go on with the arm. But it was so wide that AB had to reach out for that so much that it skews off the outside half. Straight to point who takes a reverse-cupped catch. Massive wicket. Humongous moment in the game. AB hasn't score much since SA have arrived in England, not by his standards at least.

commentary: Hasan Ali to Parnell, OUT oh my goodness, what a sensational delivery that is! Like the last one, it's angled in from around the wicket, and like the last one it straightens. This one, though, isn't quite as full as the previous ball - it's on the perfect length, leaving Parnell rooted to the crease - and its initial line is directed towards middle stump, before the movement takes it past the outside edge of the left-hander's defensive bat to crash into off stump. Top of off.

commentary: Mohammad Amir to Miller, no run given! Was that sliding down? Was there some bat? Umpire Illingworth gives it, and Miller reviews. A superb yorker, full and straight. Was there some reverse swing there? Either way, there was no bat on that as Miller fell over his shot, done in by pace and plenty of movement. Missing leg stump says HawkEye, and that decision is overturned. Good review, used judiciously through the innings and SA still in this.

commentary: Junaid Khan to Rabada, 1 run there is that yorker on middle, Pushed away to point for a run. Pakistan, led by Junaid, think this has hit Rabada's toe front. And so they review. If it was toe first, it's out. But the toe isn't close to the ball. And so it's an error from Junaid. I hope he thought it actually hit the toe first as opposed to hoping that it had. Could be crucial in a few overs

commentary: Junaid Khan to Rabada, FOUR runs that will do nicely. Good length outside off, Rabada swings, and gets bat on it. A thick outside edge through the slips region for four. The worst type of four to concede

commentary: Junaid Khan to Rabada, OUT superb catch by Hasan Ali. Full outside off, Rabada wants to go over long-on but can only skew the ball towards a slightly deep cover. Hasan tracks it early, importantly judges it early, gets across to his right, gets underneath it and takes a lovely catch. Made a terribly difficult catch look terribly simple. Asks for some noise from the crowd.

commentary: Parnell to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run back of a length outside off, lets it come on and uses his hands well to dab it to the right of backward point. Big mix-up between the batsmen as Fakhar turns back for the second before Azhar sends him back. Throw goes to the keeper's end, and that gives Fakhar just enough time to turn around, run back and dive in by the time the keeper can throw to the bowler's end. Throw misses anyway

commentary: Morkel to Fakhar Zaman, OUT superb bowling from Morkel. He's really earned this wicket. Set it up with that bouncer, and now he bowls a slower offcutter, just short of a good length on off stump. Zaman clears his front leg, perhaps looking for the pull, looking for the short ball. Picks the slower one late, only offers a feeble push, and the ball pops off the shoulder of the bat to slip

commentary: Imran Tahir to Babar Azam, no run bat-pad, or pad-bat? It's raining. Flat on off, and it hits the pad. AB reviews. De Kock said there was bat. Two clear botches on Snicko, one on the inside edge. But it looks like pad first. Definitely pad first, as is indicated by UltraEdge. Two reds, and one green. Can you believe it? Going over the stumps. Remember, it was a googly, so more revolutions on the ball and more bounce as a result.

commentary: Morkel to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT goooone! Tahir is ecstatic. He's taken a lovely catch. A nice short delivery, aimed at the badge. Hafeez plays a pull and doesn't bother keeping it down. the room for error reduces drastically when you choose that option. Gets a thick leading edge to fine leg. Tahir runs in a few metres and takes a terrific, pressure low catch. Another start for Hafeez, consumed so many balls and then got out.
